value.value: Staphylococcal toxic shock syndrome toxin 1.  A superantigen with the potential to suppress plasma cell differentiation and antibody responsiveness. Potent pyrogen, induces T lymphocyte proliferation, requiring interleukin 1 release from macrophages, suppresses immunoglobulin production, enhances endotoxin shock, and enhances hypersensitivity skin reactions. Causes staphylococcal toxic shock syndrome (TSS).
